<% content_for(:title, "Visualizations") %>

<div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-6">
  <div>
    <h1 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Visualizations</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Schema graph, volume × centrality, and field-fill density across the active run's <%= @run&.sobjects&.count || 0 %> objects.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<% if @run.nil? %>
  <div class="rounded border border-dashed border-slate-300 p-10 text-center bg-white">
    <p class="text-slate-700">No active run selected. <%= link_to "Pick one", runs_path, class: "text-blue-700 underline" %>.</p>
  </div>
<% else %>
  <%# All three sections consume the same JSON endpoint. The graph uses
      `nodes` + `clusters` + `edges`; the bubble chart uses `nodes` +
      `clusters`; the heatmap uses `heatmap` + `clusters`. Loading once
      keeps the round-trip small. %>

  <section class="rounded border border-slate-200 bg-white p-4 mb-6"
           data-controller="graph"
           data-graph-endpoint-value="<%= visualizations_data_path %>"
           data-graph-object-path-value="<%= object_path('__API_NAME__', run: @run.id) %>">
    <header class="mb-3">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold">Schema graph</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Force-directed view of all in-scope objects and relationships. Nodes are coloured by cluster and sized by field count. Scroll to zoom; drag to pan; click a node to open that object. The "Hide platform noise" toggle drops the platform scaffolding objects (User, Group, Profile, content/email/approvals) and the system-owner edges (<code>CreatedById</code>, <code>OwnerId</code>, etc.) that every object carries — about half of all edges in a Salesforce schema.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3 text-sm flex-wrap">
      <label class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5">
        <input type="checkbox" data-graph-target="hidePlatform" data-action="change->graph#togglePlatform" checked class="rounded border-slate-300">
        <span title="Hide User, Group, Profile, Network, content/email/approvals plumbing — and the CreatedById/OwnerId/LastModifiedById/RecordTypeId edges those produce on every object">Hide platform noise</span>
      </label>
      <span class="border-l border-slate-300 h-5 mx-1"></span>
      <label>Namespace:
        <select data-graph-target="namespaceFilter" class="rounded border-slate-300 text-sm">
          <option value="">All</option>
        </select>
      </label>
      <label>Min records:
        <input type="number" min="0" value="0" data-graph-target="minRecords" class="w-24 rounded border-slate-300 text-sm">
      </label>
      <button data-action="graph#applyFilters" class="rounded bg-slate-200 hover:bg-slate-300 px-2 py-1 text-xs">Apply</button>
      <span class="border-l border-slate-300 h-5 mx-1"></span>
      <button data-action="graph#zoomIn"  class="rounded bg-slate-200 hover:bg-slate-300 px-2 py-1 text-xs" title="Zoom in">＋</button>
      <button data-action="graph#zoomOut" class="rounded bg-slate-200 hover:bg-slate-300 px-2 py-1 text-xs" title="Zoom out">－</button>
      <button data-action="graph#fit"     class="rounded bg-slate-200 hover:bg-slate-300 px-2 py-1 text-xs" title="Fit to canvas">Fit</button>
    </div>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-[1fr_220px] gap-4">
      <div data-graph-target="canvas" class="bg-slate-50 rounded border border-slate-100" style="width: 100%; height: 78vh; min-height: 560px;"></div>
      <aside class="text-xs">
        <h3 class="font-medium text-slate-700 mb-1">Clusters</h3>
        <ul data-graph-target="legend" class="space-y-1"></ul>
        <p class="text-slate-500 mt-3">Clusters are auto-computed by graph modularity. Edit on <%= link_to "/clusters/edit", edit_clusters_path, class: "underline" %>.</p>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="rounded border border-slate-200 bg-white p-4 mb-6"
           data-controller="bubble-chart"
           data-bubble-chart-endpoint-value="<%= visualizations_data_path %>"
           data-bubble-chart-object-path-value="<%= object_path('__API_NAME__', run: @run.id) %>">
    <header class="mb-4">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold">Volume × centrality</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">
        Each bubble is an object. Horizontal axis is record volume (log scale); vertical axis is how many other objects point at it.
        Bubble size = field count. Colour = cluster (graph-modularity, editable on <%= link_to "/clusters/edit", edit_clusters_path, class: "underline" %>).
        Click any bubble to open that object.
      </p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-[1fr_220px] gap-4">
      <div data-bubble-chart-target="canvas" class="w-full h-[560px] border border-slate-100 rounded bg-slate-50 relative">
        <div data-bubble-chart-target="tooltip"
             class="hidden absolute pointer-events-none bg-slate-900 text-white text-xs rounded px-2 py-1 shadow z-10"></div>
      </div>
      <aside class="text-xs space-y-3">
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-medium text-slate-700 mb-1">Clusters</h3>
          <ul data-bubble-chart-target="legend" class="space-y-1"></ul>
        </div>
        <div class="text-slate-500">
          <p class="mb-1"><span class="font-medium text-slate-700">Reading the chart:</span></p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-0.5">
            <li>Top-left: critical-but-small (e.g. <code>Brand__c</code>)</li>
            <li>Top-right: workhorses (e.g. <code>Account</code>)</li>
            <li>Bottom-right: high-volume leaf data</li>
            <li>Bottom-left: cuttable noise</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="rounded border border-slate-200 bg-white p-4"
           data-controller="heatmap"
           data-heatmap-endpoint-value="<%= visualizations_data_path %>"
           data-heatmap-object-path-value="<%= object_path('__API_NAME__', run: @run.id) %>">
    <header class="mb-4">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold">Field-fill density (per object)</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">
        One row per object. Each cell is one of the object's top-filled fields, shaded by how often the field is populated (darker = more often filled).
        Objects with a lot of dense cells on the left are carrying real data; objects with a short tail are mostly empty surface.
      </p>
    </header>
    <div data-heatmap-target="canvas" class="overflow-auto max-h-[640px] border border-slate-100 rounded bg-white"></div>
  </section>
<% end %>
